Terms & Conditions

Last updated: January 1, 2024

Agreement to Terms

By accessing and using the Lume by Lee website, you accept and agree to be bound by these terms and conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use this service.

Consumer Protection Act Compliance

Lume by Lee operates in accordance with the South African Consumer Protection Act (CPA) of 2008. You have the right to fair, reasonable, and just terms. We are committed to providing quality products and services that meet your reasonable expectations.

Product Information & Pricing

All prices are displayed in South African Rand (ZAR) and include VAT where applicable. We strive to provide accurate product descriptions and pricing. Colors may vary due to monitor settings and photography lighting. We reserve the right to correct pricing errors.

Payment & Delivery

Payment must be received before dispatch of goods. We deliver nationwide via PEP and The Courier Guy to parcel lockers within 5-7 business days. Delivery costs will be calculated at checkout based on your location.

Returns & Exchanges

We offer size exchanges within 7 days of delivery. Items must be unworn, unwashed, and in original condition with tags attached. Refunds are not available, but we will exchange for a different size subject to availability. Customer is responsible for return shipping costs.

Privacy & Data Protection

We comply with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA). Your personal information is collected and processed in accordance with our Privacy Policy. We will not share your information with third parties without your consent.

Limitation of Liability

Our liability is limited to the extent permitted by South African law. We are not liable for indirect, consequential, or special damages. Our maximum liability shall not exceed the purchase price of the product.

Governing Law & Jurisdiction

These terms are governed by South African law. Any disputes will be subject to the jurisdiction of the South African courts. You may also refer disputes to the National Consumer Commission or relevant Ombud services.

Questions about our Terms?

Contact us at privacy@lumebylee.co.za
